    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>peroral endoscopic myotomy</intervention_name>
    <description>The procedure consists of four steps: 1) mucosal incision 10-15 cm above the esophagogastric junction to allow entry into the submucosa, 2) creation of a submucosal tunnel until the lower esophageal sphincter is reached, 3) myotomy of the circular muscle layer, and 4) closure of the mucosal entry with endoclips.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Peroral endoscopic myotomy (POEM)</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
